Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
set_glitch_derate(25.10)                              set_glitch_derate(25.10)

Name
       set_glitch_derate  - Sets the derating factors for glitch waveforms and
       determines the effect of on-chip variation on noise

Syntax
       set_glitch_derate

       [-help]

       [-derate_height <float>]

        [-derate_width <float>]

        [-glitch_type <string>]

        [-instance_pin <string>]

       [-offset <float>]

        [-pin <string>]

        [-view <string>]

       Sets the derating factors for glitch waveforms and determines  the  ef-
       fect of on-chip variation on noise.

Parameters
       -help  Prints out the command usage.

       -derate_height <float>
              Specifies the derate height value.

              This  parameter scales all the glitch waveforms on the specified
              pins.

              A value of 1.0 indicates that no glitch waveform  derating  will
              take  place.  A value greater than 1.0, such as 1.1, indicates a
              10 percent increase in the  magnitude  of  the  complete  glitch
              waveform,  which  results in an increase in propagated noise and
              noise failure. A value less than 1.0 reduces  the  magnitude  of
              the complete glitch waveform.

       -derate_width <float>
              Specifies the derate width value.

       -glitch_type <string>
              Specifies the glitch type - vl, vh, or all.

       -instance_pin <string>
              Specifies  the  instance  pin names on which derate is to be ap-
              plied.

       -offset <float>
              Specifies the derate offset value.

       -pin <string>
              Specifies the library pin names on which derate value is  to  be
              applied.

       -view <string>
              Specifies the name of the view.

Related Information
              * reset_glitch_derate

              * update_glitch

